line_1: Perch'd on her Bough the wanton Chirper mocks
line_2: The quiet harmless Posture of the Fox.

line_1: And tho' witlings may scoff, and tho' raillery mocks,
line_2: Yet I'll sing to my lass with the golden locks.

line_1: At all attempts to catch it mocks,
line_2: And ne'er was brought t'an Equinox:

line_1: May taunt you wi' his jeers an' mocks;
May taunt you wi' his jeers an' mocks;
line_2: But gie him't het, my hearty cocks!

line_2: An' send him to his dicing box,
